Detailed Character Set Comparison

This document describes how similar any two Unicode conversion tables are to each other. Please see http://www.unicode.org/unicode/reports/tr22/ for the character mapping details. If you would like more information on this topic, like alias tables or location of these mappings, please go to the main page. Style sheets must be enabled in your web browser to properly view these results. These results are preliminary.

Options used to generate this document

Document generated on Mon Dec 13 14:35:27 PST 2004
Roundtrip threshold: 90.0%
Subset threshold: 10.0%
Compare ISO control characters: true
Show minimum number: true
Show fallback results: true
Show reverse fallback results: false

Definition of terms

The "RT(%)" column means "roundtrip percent"
The "FB(%)" column means "fallback percent"
Green means identical.
Yellow means different set sizes.
Cyan means best match.

The equation used to calculate an entry in a table is "minimum( sizeof(A intersects B)/ sizeof(A), sizeof(A intersects B) / sizeof(B))". This equation can also look like this "min( | A ∩ B | / | A |, | A ∩ B | / | B |)" where A is a set of mappings for a codepage, and B is a different set of mappings for a codepage that is being compared to A.
